Class Identifiers

java.lang.Object
Identifiers
public class Identifiers extends Object
Demonstrates Java identifier rules and naming conventions.

Definition

Identifiers are names given to variables, parameters, methods, fields, classes, interfaces, enums, records, annotations and packages.

Rules

  1. The first character must be a Java letter, which includes:
    • Roman alphabet letters (a-z, A-Z)
    • Dollar sign ($)
    • Underscore (_)
    • Unicode letters (e.g., π, 你好)
  2. Subsequent characters can be any Java letter or Java digit, which includes:
    • All characters allowed as first character
    • Arabic numerals (0-9)
    • Unicode digits (e.g., ٠, १, ๒)
  3. The underscore character (_) is allowed but discouraged except in constant names
  4. The dollar sign ($) is allowed but should be used only in generated code
  5. There is no practical limit to the length of an identifier, but it's recommended to keep them meaningful and concise

Naming Conventions

  • AbcDef: roman alphabet letters starting with an uppercase letter and following the camel case for class, record, interface, enum or annotation names (e.g., UserService, DataTransformer)
  • ABC_DEF: uppercase roman alphabet letters separated by underscores for class constants (e.g., MAX_RETRY_COUNT, DEFAULT_TIMEZONE)
  • abcDef: roman alphabet letters starting with a lowercase letter and following the camel case for variable, method parameter, method, field and package names (e.g., userInput, processUserData)
  • E: a single roman alphabet uppercase letter for class, record or interface parameter (e.g., GenericClass<E>, Box<T>)

Package Name Rules

  • They cannot have hyphens
  • They cannot end with the point symbol
  • They should be all lowercase
  • They should follow the reverse domain name convention (e.g., com.example.project)
  • They should be meaningful and reflect the project structure

Reserved Keywords

The following 53 keywords cannot be used as identifiers:

  • abstract, assert
  • boolean, break, byte
  • case, catch, char, class, const, continue
  • default, do, double
  • else, enum, extends
  • false, final, finally, float, for
  • goto
  • if, implements, import, instanceof, int, interface
  • long
  • native, new, null
  • package, private, protected, public
  • return
  • short, static, strictfp, super, switch, synchronized
  • this, throw, throws, transient, true, try
  • void, volatile
  • while

Examples

  • Conventional: userName, MAX_COUNT, UserService
  • Unicode letters: π, 你好, こんにちは
  • Unicode digits: user١, count๒
  • With underscore: user_name (discouraged), MAX_RETRY_COUNT (allowed for constants)
  • With dollar: $generated (discouraged except in generated code)
